      "role": "user",
      "content": "but u said it's \"co-opted by both sides\" which sounds like a way to dodge the question. if you look at how it actually works in the real world, like in universities or media, isn't it mostly just people being afraid to speak their minds because they might get \"canceled\"? feels like the censorship part is more of a fact than an opinion.",
